The State  moves to delete the enhancers on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1, deliver Clonazepam.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served, to commence upon the defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Provide DNA sample;
5) Pay court costs including $80.00 buy money;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) maintain fulltime employment/work search;
8) defendant is to use only one doctor to prescribe medications and only one pharmacist to dispense medications unless approved by the agent;
9) maintain absolute sobriety.
Minutes.
